# HADES Script Collection - Project Structure Guide

This is a comprehensive script collection management system called "HADES" (Script Collection Management System). The main entry point is [install.sh](mdc:install.sh), which provides an interactive installer for managing and executing scripts.

## Project Structure

### Core Files
- [install.sh](mdc:install.sh) - Main installer and script executor with interactive menu system
- [README.md](mdc:README.md) - Project documentation and usage instructions
- [backups.sh](mdc:backups.sh) - Backup management script
- [test.sh](mdc:test.sh) - Testing utilities

### Script Categories
The `script/` directory contains organized categories:

- **ai-tools/** - AI development tools and utilities
  - [opencode.sh](mdc:script/ai-tools/opencode.sh) - OpenCode AI installation script
  
- **dev-tools/** - Development environment setup
  - [docker-install.sh](mdc:script/dev-tools/docker-install.sh) - Docker installation
  - [install-dev-tools.sh](mdc:script/dev-tools/install-dev-tools.sh) - Development tools installer
  - [tmux-install.sh](mdc:script/dev-tools/tmux-install.sh) - Tmux installation
  - [zsh-tmux.sh](mdc:script/dev-tools/zsh-tmux.sh) - Zsh and Tmux configuration
  - [connect-gh.sh](mdc:script/dev-tools/connect-gh.sh) - GitHub connection utilities

- **vm-test/** - VPS security hardening and testing
  - [harden-server.sh](mdc:script/vm-test/harden-server.sh) - Server hardening script
  - [vps-check.sh](mdc:script/vm-test/vps-check.sh) - VPS health checks
  - [vps-sec-check.sh](mdc:script/vm-test/vps-sec-check.sh) - Security audit script
  - [ssh-config.sh](mdc:script/vm-test/ssh-config.sh) - SSH configuration
  - [aktif-otp.sh](mdc:script/vm-test/aktif-otp.sh) - OTP activation
  - [docs/](mdc:script/vm-test/docs/) - Documentation for security scripts

- **setupOS/** - Operating system setup scripts
  - [omakub.sh](mdc:script/setupOS/omakub.sh) - Ubuntu setup
  - [omarchy.sh](mdc:script/setupOS/omarchy.sh) - Arch Linux setup

- **jaringan/** - Network configuration scripts
- **password-generator/** - Password generation utilities
- **dev-env/** - Development environment configuration

## Key Features
- Interactive script selection with category-based organization
- Support for multiple script execution
- Automatic sudo detection and handling
- Comprehensive error handling and logging
- Beautiful terminal UI with colors and emojis
- Idempotent script execution (safe to run multiple times)

## Usage Patterns
- Scripts are organized by functionality in subdirectories
- Each script should be executable and include proper error handling
- Scripts should be idempotent when possible
- Security scripts in vm-test/ require sudo privileges
- All scripts follow bash best practices with `set -euo pipefail`